"title": "5472: proof, as evidence",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5472: proof, as evidence",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In the judicial sense, evidence is required to confirm the testimony of a witness. In the lives of believers, practical evidence should be obvious as proof of the reality of their faith.</p>\n<h2>The Mosaic law required proof to be offered in various legal contexts</h2>\n<h3>In giving testimony</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:15\">DEU 19:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:2\">EXO 23:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:1\">LEV 5:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:6\">DEU 17:6</a></p>\n<h3>In acccusations of immorality</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:13-Deut22:21\">DEU 22:13–22:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:11-Num5:31\">NUM 5:11–5:31</a></p>\n<h3>In accusations of idolatry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:12-Deut13:15\">DEU 13:12–13:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Evidence offered as proof of the gospel</h2>\n<h3>The evidence of witnesses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:16-2Pet1:18\">2PE 1:16–1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:3\">ACT 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:5-1Cor15:7\">1CO 15:5–15:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:3-Heb2:4\">HEB 2:3–2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:1-1John1:3\">1JN 1:1–1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Believers' lives are to prove the reality of their faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:8\">JHN 15:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:46\">MAT 25:31–25:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:20\">ACT 26:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:2\">1CO 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:24\">2CO 8:24</a></p>\n<h2>Evidence and signs given as proof</h2>\n<h3>Looking for signs of the will of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:36-Judg6:38\">JDG 6:36–6:38</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The signs of Jesus Christ as a basis of faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:11\">JHN 2:11</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's criticism of those who demanded other signs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:4\">MAT 16:4</a></strong> <em>The “sign of Jonah” is a reference to the resurrection of Jesus Christ.</em></p>",
